  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The publication \"Glass Making in the Greco-Roman World: Results of the ARCHGLASS project\" serves as a significant scholarly resource elucidating the complexities of ancient glass production. With an implication of active scholarly uptake, as indicated by 40 citations, it stands as a valuable contribution to the understanding of historical glassmaking practices.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published in 2015 by Leuven University Press, \"Glass Making in the Greco-Roman World: Results of the ARCHGLASS project\" presents comprehensive findings on the art and technology of glass-making during the Greco-Roman era. This scholarly work not only preserves the legacy of ancient craftsmanship but also enriches current academic discourse with its substantial citations, totaling 40, reflecting its impact within the field.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The ARCHGLASS project shines a light on the significance of ancient glass making, emphasizing its artistic and technological merits. This investigation is crucial for scholars examining historical material culture, as it provides key insights and data. The citation metrics align with a growing interest in interdisciplinary studies related to historical craftsmanship, revealing the publication\u2019s role in bridging past and present academic inquiries.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite the absence of online discourse and social mentions, the work\u2019s academic credibility remains intact through its recognition by reputable platforms like Amazon and Goodreads, indicating a latent commercial interest. This reflects a dual appreciation for both the scholarly community and the public's potential curiosity in historical artifacts and technologies.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Overall, the contribution of this work to the field cannot be understated, as it offers foundational insights that serve not only to academic professionals but also to a broader audience intrigued by the ancient world. The scholarly uptake and recognition underscore the relevance and importance of historical studies in contemporary discourse.</p>",
